1
00:00:55,556 --> 00:00:56,557
{\an8}EPISODE 8

2
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:57,641
{\an8}[Jun-beom] Hmm…

3
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:04,356
{\an8}The truth is, I used to have nothing,
like an orphan in the middle of a war.

4
00:01:06,108 --> 00:01:11,489
{\an8}It takes a very thick mask to stand there
and pretend that everything is fine.

5
00:01:12,198 --> 00:01:13,866
{\an8}Who are you, really?

6
00:01:14,784 --> 00:01:18,579
{\an8}Why did you approach me
when you already knew Su-ho?

7
00:01:18,662 --> 00:01:20,915
{\an8}[intense music plays]

8
00:01:31,801 --> 00:01:34,929
{\an8}Do you think I'm trying to blame you
for Su-ho's death?

9
00:01:36,472 --> 00:01:37,973
Is that what you think?

10
00:01:40,392 --> 00:01:42,144
[dramatic music plays]

11
00:01:42,812 --> 00:01:43,813
Do you think…

12
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:47,817
I'm getting revenge on you for him?

13
00:01:57,034 --> 00:01:58,035
[scoffs]

14
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:03,707
I watching Su-ho be happy and sad.

15
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:06,919
Also tormented all because of
a woman named Han Seol-ah.

16
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:10,631
And I always wondered,
"What kind of person is she?"

17
00:02:11,507 --> 00:02:14,218
The moment I saw you,
I understood everything.

18
00:02:15,302 --> 00:02:19,265
She's the kind of woman
a man would risk his life for.

19
00:02:20,683 --> 00:02:21,684
So then…

20
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:28,941
Are you saying you ended up falling for
the woman who caused your friend's death?

21
00:02:30,568 --> 00:02:31,694
[Jun-beom] Hmm…

22
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:37,575
If Su-ho were still alive, I wouldn't
have dared to even think about it.

23
00:02:38,242 --> 00:02:40,160
But my friend's no longer in this world,

24
00:02:40,244 --> 00:02:45,291
and you and I are here,
under the same sky.

25
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,006
Anything else?

26
00:02:53,257 --> 00:02:54,925
Do you need to hear another truth?

27
00:03:00,556 --> 00:03:02,933
[fire alarm blaring]

28
00:03:03,017 --> 00:03:04,268
[Jun-beom gasps]

29
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:11,692
J.B. PAEK

30
00:03:15,279 --> 00:03:17,239
[breathing heavily, grunting]

31
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:23,871
Sir. Are you all right, sir?

32
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:25,372
[groans] What's going on?

33
00:03:25,456 --> 00:03:27,583
The fire alarm went off.
We're checking on it.

34
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:29,168
Find out what's going on!

35
00:03:29,251 --> 00:03:30,544
Yes, sir.

36
00:03:32,463 --> 00:03:33,464
[door closes]

37
00:03:34,757 --> 00:03:35,758
Let's finish this later.

38
00:03:40,596 --> 00:03:43,182
[panting]

39
00:03:44,767 --> 00:03:46,852
[person on PA]
<i>Due to the fire alarm being activated,</i>

40
00:03:46,936 --> 00:03:50,064
<i>all employees are requested</i>
<i>to evacuate the building.</i>

41
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,815
<i>Please avoid the elevators</i>

42
00:03:51,899 --> 00:03:54,652
<i>and use the stairs</i>
<i>to find your nearest exit.</i>

43
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:02,576
Get in, quick!

44
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,668
YOUR HOME
CONTROL CENTER

45
00:04:10,751 --> 00:04:12,002
Stop right there.

46
00:04:13,045 --> 00:04:15,089
[breathes shakily]

47
00:04:17,675 --> 00:04:18,676
Next one.

48
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:24,431
Another angle.

49
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,022
Stop, right there.

50
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:38,696
Nice black cap…

51
00:04:41,824 --> 00:04:43,158
{\an8}103S 4549

52
00:04:54,712 --> 00:04:56,338
{\an8}103S 4549

53
00:05:00,050 --> 00:05:02,136
So, it was Mr. Paek who…

54
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:03,679
He's the one who ordered the hit.

55
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:07,933
The alarm suddenly went off earlier,
so I couldn't press him for more, but…

56
00:05:08,017 --> 00:05:09,018
I did that.

57
00:05:10,436 --> 00:05:12,312
I was worried you'd be in danger.

58
00:05:35,044 --> 00:05:36,045
[phone beeps]

59
00:05:36,128 --> 00:05:38,547
[line ringing]

60
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:40,466
[Jun-beom] My office
will handle the arrangements.

61
00:05:40,549 --> 00:05:42,134
Stay overseas for a while.

62
00:05:44,261 --> 00:05:45,262
[phone beeps]

63
00:05:49,308 --> 00:05:51,310
[sighs]

64
00:05:53,145 --> 00:05:55,731
I didn't think this day
would come so soon.

65
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:02,613
If Mr. Paek tried to have
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin killed,

66
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:05,532
could it mean he's done this before?

67
00:06:05,616 --> 00:06:08,160
Yeah, there's a good chance
that he might have.

68
00:06:09,244 --> 00:06:10,245
I don't get it.

69
00:06:10,329 --> 00:06:14,792
Even if this is revenge on Su-ho's behalf,
this is way too extreme.

70
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,212
I think Paek Jun-beom

71
00:06:19,046 --> 00:06:21,840
already knows what information
was taken from the server,

72
00:06:21,924 --> 00:06:24,176
and in that state, he'll do anything.

73
00:06:25,094 --> 00:06:27,513
If we track his movements
after Syria and put pressure on him--

74
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:30,516
Then what if you become
his next target, Woo-seok?

75
00:06:31,809 --> 00:06:33,143
It'd be even better.

76
00:06:34,019 --> 00:06:35,729
His henchman's been exposed.

77
00:06:35,813 --> 00:06:37,981
Paek Jun-beom will have to
trip himself up now.

78
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:39,942
Why are you being so reckless?

79
00:06:41,860 --> 00:06:43,320
Are you worried about me?

80
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:45,531
Yes, of course.

81
00:06:49,493 --> 00:06:50,953
Well, that's enough for me.

82
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:58,752
[Woo-seok chuckles]

83
00:07:01,672 --> 00:07:03,924
{\an8}AHN *****-SOO / M / 980205

84
00:07:07,511 --> 00:07:10,264
Mr. Ahn, how long
do I have to keep hiding?

85
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:11,807
I'm tired of this.

86
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,935
We're just worried
you'll be in danger again.

87
00:07:15,811 --> 00:07:20,190
My wife thinks I'm having an affair
because I won't even tell her where I am.

88
00:07:20,941 --> 00:07:23,819
Mr. Ahn. Looks like you're out. [chuckles]

89
00:07:24,403 --> 00:07:26,113
Want play poker now or what?

90
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:28,532
- Mr. Cha!
- Hey.

91
00:07:30,993 --> 00:07:31,994
Feeling any better?

92
00:07:32,077 --> 00:07:35,539
[chuckles] The doctor said
it'd be good to relieve some stress,

93
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:37,916
so I'm recovering
by emptying Mr. Ahn's wallet.

94
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,043
- [chuckles]
- He's a killer at cards.

95
00:07:40,127 --> 00:07:42,796
Oh, man… [chuckles]

96
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:47,551
[Kwang-jin gasps]

97
00:07:48,177 --> 00:07:49,178
Jun-beom…

98
00:07:50,053 --> 00:07:51,388
Why would Jun-beom target me?

99
00:07:52,181 --> 00:07:53,557
I just can't believe it.

100
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:56,101
He just didn't want the two of us to meet.

101
00:07:56,185 --> 00:07:58,061
There's definitely more

102
00:07:58,687 --> 00:08:01,023
to the relationship between
Lee Su-ho and Paek Jun-beom.

103
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:04,151
[sighs] The Jun-beom I know
has no reason to do this.

104
00:08:04,234 --> 00:08:06,945
He's not the type
to do something like this.

105
00:08:07,029 --> 00:08:09,531
A shameful secret
that shouldn't be known to the world.

106
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,743
Something no one should ever know.

107
00:08:13,744 --> 00:08:16,371
[sighs] I can't think of anything.

108
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:18,332
[sighs]

109
00:08:18,415 --> 00:08:21,126
[sighs] Well, if you happen to,
then please let me know.

110
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,171
I've almost got this puzzle solved…

111
00:08:25,297 --> 00:08:26,548
but there's a piece missing.

112
00:08:27,799 --> 00:08:29,009
The most important one.

113
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:31,929
GANGHA POLICE STATION

114
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:34,056
- [door opens]
- They've issued a travel ban

115
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:35,307
on Kim Sung-hae.

116
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:38,393
Hit-and-run, attempted murder.

117
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:41,021
There's more than enough evidence. [sighs]

118
00:08:41,104 --> 00:08:42,648
The problem is Paek Jun-beom.

119
00:08:42,731 --> 00:08:46,360
This illegal evidence from Woo-seok
isn't enough to charge him with murder.

120
00:08:46,443 --> 00:08:49,279
Do you think that he also had
Kim Sung-hae kill Kim Yun-ji?

121
00:08:49,363 --> 00:08:51,573
That doesn't explain
Paek Jun-beom's motive, though.

122
00:08:51,657 --> 00:08:54,034
He's got a lot to lose. [sighs]

123
00:08:54,117 --> 00:08:57,079
In cases like this,
isn't it love or a grudge?

124
00:08:57,162 --> 00:08:58,622
[Seong-il inhales sharply]

125
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:02,751
Let's bring him in as a witness then,
and we'll see what kind of person he is.

126
00:09:02,834 --> 00:09:03,919
All right.

127
00:09:04,002 --> 00:09:05,796
- [knocks on door]
- [door opens]

128
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:08,465
Oh, hello there.

129
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,926
- You're here.
- What's up?

130
00:09:11,009 --> 00:09:13,095
I called, but you didn't answer.

131
00:09:13,178 --> 00:09:14,388
You called me?

132
00:09:14,471 --> 00:09:18,767
Captain, why don't you just
head back home with your wife tonight?

133
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:21,853
Oh, I just wanted to drop off
some clothes for him

134
00:09:21,937 --> 00:09:23,146
and some snacks for you guys.

135
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:25,607
You haven't had
a proper meal yet, have you?

136
00:09:28,694 --> 00:09:32,364
Wow, this isn't just any midnight snack.
It's Chungmu gimbap.

137
00:09:32,447 --> 00:09:34,741
Most people get bored of regular gimbap.

138
00:09:34,825 --> 00:09:37,119
- [Gong] We will definitely enjoy this.
- [chuckles]

139
00:09:48,171 --> 00:09:49,840
[Seong-il] Come on.
Let's sit down and eat.

140
00:09:49,923 --> 00:09:51,383
[Eun-gyeom] Oh, this looks delicious.

141
00:09:52,551 --> 00:09:53,552
[chuckles]

142
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:07,399
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

143
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:08,942
[employees chattering]

144
00:10:09,026 --> 00:10:11,611
[Won-il] Taemyung Cultural
Foundation's accident?

145
00:10:14,031 --> 00:10:15,115
{\an8}FINE ART
INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

146
00:10:15,198 --> 00:10:17,868
A cargo truck crashed into
the retaining wall and started a fire,

147
00:10:17,951 --> 00:10:19,953
and five artworks were destroyed.

148
00:10:20,037 --> 00:10:22,831
The insured amount alone is $7 million.

149
00:10:24,041 --> 00:10:26,001
DRIVING RECORD CERTIFICATE
NAME: HAN SEO-YUL

150
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:30,172
The driver is only 23
and hasn't had his license a year.

151
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:34,384
When moving high-value paintings
like these, you never do it alone.

152
00:10:34,468 --> 00:10:36,178
[machines whirring]

153
00:10:41,224 --> 00:10:42,893
[Woo-seok]
<i>A team of professionals is sent.</i>

154
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,603
FROM ARTIST STUDIOS TO YOU

155
00:10:51,443 --> 00:10:52,652
[engine starts]

156
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:56,281
[Woo-seok] <i>They also send</i>
<i>the ones with the most experience.</i>

157
00:10:57,783 --> 00:11:00,077
There's no way that they would
handle this this carelessly.

158
00:11:00,911 --> 00:11:01,912
[sighs]

159
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:04,081
It's possible this whole thing was staged.

160
00:11:04,164 --> 00:11:07,834
- Anyway, get in touch with the GI's SIU.
- [sighs]

161
00:11:08,335 --> 00:11:10,587
This case doesn't belong here. Not here.

162
00:11:11,088 --> 00:11:14,049
We actually need some help
from an art expert,

163
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:18,762
and I hear you and Ms. Han
from Royal Auction

164
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:21,973
have gotten a bit closer.

165
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:23,725
Who said that?

166
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:30,774
[sighs]

167
00:11:32,818 --> 00:11:33,819
I'll ask her.

168
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:35,487
[sighs] Thank you so much.

169
00:11:37,239 --> 00:11:38,240
[sighs]

170
00:11:40,409 --> 00:11:43,412
Can you tell me how many bidders
we've secured so far

171
00:11:43,495 --> 00:11:45,038
for the Stiller piece?

172
00:11:45,122 --> 00:11:47,707
Eleven so far,
both phone and written bids.

173
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:51,920
Only three are confirmed so far,
but we're still actively promoting it.

174
00:11:52,003 --> 00:11:54,631
The price is so high, the hurdle is steep.

175
00:11:54,714 --> 00:11:57,717
Same here.
Three people interested in the piece.

176
00:11:59,636 --> 00:12:03,098
Early bids will determine
the momentum we have on this lot.

177
00:12:03,181 --> 00:12:06,685
We need to make sure there's competition,

178
00:12:06,768 --> 00:12:10,355
so please reach out to our VIPs again
and keep me updated.

179
00:12:10,439 --> 00:12:11,481
Sure.

180
00:12:11,565 --> 00:12:13,191
About the catalog…

181
00:12:19,364 --> 00:12:22,784
Sang-mi, I'd like you
to complete the final review.

182
00:12:22,868 --> 00:12:25,662
- Yes, Ms. Han.
- All right, that is it for today.

183
00:12:30,584 --> 00:12:35,881
[inhales sharply] Oh, wait, wasn't that
something Yun-ji always handled?

184
00:12:35,964 --> 00:12:40,510
Does that mean you might be going up
on the rostrum as an assistant this time?

185
00:12:41,303 --> 00:12:44,931
Not sure. Who knows
what Ms. Han might be thinking?

186
00:12:45,015 --> 00:12:46,349
Oh, man…

187
00:12:57,277 --> 00:12:58,445
[dramatic music plays]

188
00:12:58,528 --> 00:12:59,988
FINE ART
INSURANCE CLAIM FORM

189
00:13:07,746 --> 00:13:09,623
[prosecutor] The defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

190
00:13:09,706 --> 00:13:12,667
intentionally crashed
into a retaining wall on an entrance ramp,

191
00:13:12,751 --> 00:13:14,920
causing the death of his passenger,
Cha Woo-hee.

192
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,672
The evidence at the scene,
and the defendant's insurance records,

193
00:13:17,756 --> 00:13:19,799
demonstrate that he acted
with intent to kill.

194
00:13:19,883 --> 00:13:22,219
The prosecution requests
the court sentence the defendant

195
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:23,637
to ten years' imprisonment.

196
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:26,139
[sighs]

197
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:34,397
- [phone beeps]
- [line rings]

198
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,108
[phone buzzing]

199
00:13:37,192 --> 00:13:38,193
[colleague chuckles]

200
00:13:38,276 --> 00:13:40,362
INCOMING CALL
WOO-SEOK

201
00:13:41,071 --> 00:13:43,907
Wow, you're psychic.
I was just about to call you.

202
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:45,909
Anything on Ju Hyun-su?

203
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:49,955
So, someone signed up
for a food delivery app using his email.

204
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:51,289
About a month ago.

205
00:13:52,874 --> 00:13:54,167
Get me the address. Fast!

206
00:13:54,251 --> 00:13:55,877
[colleague] <i>All right, got it.</i>

207
00:14:19,901 --> 00:14:21,152
[gate beeps]

208
00:14:25,782 --> 00:14:26,992
[elevator bell dings]

209
00:14:32,455 --> 00:14:33,456
[elevator doors shut]

210
00:14:38,962 --> 00:14:42,048
{\an8}ROYAL AUCTION
JU HYUN-SU

211
00:15:04,613 --> 00:15:06,156
[elevator bell dings]

212
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:17,751
[ethereal music playing]

213
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,976
[door closes]

214
00:15:35,060 --> 00:15:37,062
[ethereal music continues]

215
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:47,697
I thought I told you
to stay away from the auction house.

216
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:49,491
I'm family too.

217
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:53,536
I just wanted to see what it was like
to check in like everyone else.

218
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:57,791
Didn't I tell you not to act rashly?

219
00:15:57,874 --> 00:16:00,460
The Taemyung deal has to wrap up smoothly.

220
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,090
No need to worry.

221
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:08,343
I've given it my all.
I mean, it is my comeback project.

222
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:12,597
I should at least get a taste of
one of your famous spreads, ma'am.

223
00:16:12,681 --> 00:16:13,682
[scoffs]

224
00:16:13,765 --> 00:16:16,893
Once the Taemyung deal's wrapped up,
hook me up with a stake too.

225
00:16:18,395 --> 00:16:19,604
I won't be greedy.

226
00:16:19,688 --> 00:16:22,649
How about 10%?

227
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:24,567
[scoffs]

228
00:16:26,778 --> 00:16:28,738
You've grown a lot, Ju Hyun-su.

229
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:31,574
You've raised me well, ma'am.

230
00:16:49,008 --> 00:16:51,136
[mysterious music plays]

231
00:17:07,152 --> 00:17:08,737
[Seol-ah] I saw the accident on the news.

232
00:17:08,820 --> 00:17:11,197
Is there a problem with the insurance?

233
00:17:11,281 --> 00:17:12,282
The thing is…

234
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:15,410
It's similar to my sister's accident.

235
00:17:16,453 --> 00:17:17,746
What do you mean?

236
00:17:17,829 --> 00:17:22,500
The crash happened on the same curve
near Namcheonghyeon Interchange,

237
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:24,627
hitting the passenger side only.

238
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,505
Apart from the fire,
everything is the same.

239
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:32,385
Criminals stick to familiar tactics
and repeat methods that worked before.

240
00:17:33,428 --> 00:17:35,680
I want to check if it was planned
by the same person.

241
00:17:39,267 --> 00:17:40,769
I need your help, Seol-ah.

242
00:17:52,822 --> 00:17:55,283
I handled the auctions
of all these pieces.

243
00:17:55,366 --> 00:17:57,619
They were listed by an overseas gallery,

244
00:17:57,702 --> 00:18:00,371
but when I looked into it,
it turned out to be a shell company.

245
00:18:00,455 --> 00:18:02,957
And the real owner is our chairwoman.

246
00:18:04,793 --> 00:18:05,794
Chair Kim?

247
00:18:05,877 --> 00:18:08,963
She chooses artworks that will be
profitable for wealthy clients,

248
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:10,632
and takes a cut herself.

249
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:16,137
Taemyung bought this piece
for 1.05 million dollars,

250
00:18:16,805 --> 00:18:20,099
but it was imported from overseas
for about 210,000.

251
00:18:21,476 --> 00:18:22,477
Is that possible?

252
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:25,104
You see, paintings don't have set prices.

253
00:18:25,188 --> 00:18:30,735
If someone pays 1.05 million for one,
that becomes the piece's real value.

254
00:18:31,319 --> 00:18:32,320
Oh, I see.

255
00:18:33,655 --> 00:18:36,991
So if the paintings were insured
and someone deliberately burned them,

256
00:18:37,075 --> 00:18:39,577
they could collect the full 1.05 million?

257
00:18:39,661 --> 00:18:42,664
People in the art world
would never do that though.

258
00:18:43,581 --> 00:18:47,460
There's no way
they'd destroy an authentic artwork.

259
00:18:47,544 --> 00:18:49,003
They'd sneak out the authentic piece.

260
00:18:49,087 --> 00:18:50,964
And then burn the fake.

261
00:18:54,384 --> 00:18:57,303
That is Chair Kim's way of doing things.

262
00:19:01,307 --> 00:19:02,392
[Woo-seok sighs]

263
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:06,062
[scoffs]

264
00:19:07,063 --> 00:19:13,069
A struggling artist was hired by Chair Kim
to create a replica of a particular piece.

265
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:20,326
But later, the work was passed off as
the original, and sparked a huge scandal.

266
00:19:20,410 --> 00:19:22,912
[artist groans, yelps]

267
00:19:22,996 --> 00:19:24,080
- [wails]
- [loan shark] Oh, no.

268
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:28,751
No, my hand! No! [screaming, sobbing]

269
00:19:29,294 --> 00:19:31,296
[Han wails]

270
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:37,594
If you're going to be shameless,
at least own up to it.

271
00:19:37,677 --> 00:19:40,138
Borrowing from loan sharks? Bold move.

272
00:19:40,221 --> 00:19:42,432
Now look at the mess you're in, Mr. Han.

273
00:19:42,515 --> 00:19:45,226
- Your hand…
- [Han screaming, sobbing]

274
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:48,813
- I'm begging you!
- How are you gonna hold a brush

275
00:19:48,897 --> 00:19:50,148
with a hand like that?

276
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:53,735
That's the only thing about you
that still works.

277
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:59,616
If this ends up being a posthumous work,

278
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:02,452
I'll make sure it sells for a high price.

279
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:04,495
No! Please, I'm begging you.

280
00:20:04,579 --> 00:20:06,080
Just let me keep it!

281
00:20:06,164 --> 00:20:11,669
The naive artist thought he was just
painting a replica for an exhibition,

282
00:20:12,670 --> 00:20:13,922
but he took the fall…

283
00:20:15,632 --> 00:20:17,091
for everything.

284
00:20:19,969 --> 00:20:24,849
Later, he was hounded by loan sharks
and died with his family.

285
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:27,477
Could the artist be…

286
00:20:30,939 --> 00:20:32,315
He was my father.

287
00:20:35,026 --> 00:20:40,573
I want to prove to the world
that my father wasn't that kind of person.

288
00:20:42,325 --> 00:20:43,743
So, you joined Royal Auction--

289
00:20:43,826 --> 00:20:45,244
[Seol-ah] Because I wanted revenge.

290
00:20:46,829 --> 00:20:52,293
And now, it's become
the only reason I have to go on living.

291
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:56,714
I know how that feels.

292
00:20:58,091 --> 00:21:01,344
I am also after the person
who ruined my life.

293
00:21:07,517 --> 00:21:09,477
We need to find the paintings. [sighs]

294
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:11,479
The ones that were supposedly burned.

295
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:15,400
There's a secret vault
in Chair Kim's office.

296
00:21:31,374 --> 00:21:35,503
I've been wanting to get in for
a long time but never had the opportunity.

297
00:21:36,004 --> 00:21:38,423
You're going to need
someone like me for this.

298
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:44,095
And I need an art insider
to solve this fraud case.

299
00:21:47,015 --> 00:21:48,766
Then let's uncover them.

300
00:21:50,601 --> 00:21:53,271
Let's uncover the hidden truths together.

301
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,482
[exhales sharply]

302
00:22:18,129 --> 00:22:21,883
Damn it, why's this office so soundproof?

303
00:22:21,966 --> 00:22:22,967
Shit.

304
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:30,516
- Hey, what are you doing?
- [gasps]

305
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:33,436
Damn, you scared me. Geez…

306
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:35,813
- There's someone in there.
- Really?

307
00:22:36,647 --> 00:22:39,025
Well, it was dead quiet.
I thought it was empty.

308
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:41,027
[clears throat, clicks tongue]

309
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:42,111
I'm off.

310
00:22:53,581 --> 00:22:55,625
MEET CHA WOO-SEOK, THE GRIM
REAPER OF INSURANCE FRAUD!

311
00:23:02,298 --> 00:23:05,927
He looks like an upright, dependable guy,
based on his features.

312
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:11,641
Is there anything else
you need me to do, ma'am?

313
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:14,435
You know I can be just as good as Yun-ji.

314
00:23:15,436 --> 00:23:17,647
Do you know Ms. Kim's responsibilities?

315
00:23:18,439 --> 00:23:20,108
I know, to some extent.

316
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:23,694
I may not be there yet,
but I'll learn step by step.

317
00:23:23,778 --> 00:23:27,990
What I'm looking for
isn't someone at Ms. Kim's level,

318
00:23:28,074 --> 00:23:30,284
but someone at Ms. Han's.

319
00:23:30,368 --> 00:23:34,163
You should be aiming to reach
Han Seol-ah's level, at the very least.

320
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:37,041
For now,
just keep reporting to me like this.

321
00:23:37,625 --> 00:23:40,962
Yes, ma'am. I'll make sure
to keep reporting like this from now on.

322
00:23:49,137 --> 00:23:51,722
[Seol-ah] Mr. Paek sent me this painting.

323
00:23:51,806 --> 00:23:53,641
There should be a clue in here.

324
00:23:55,768 --> 00:23:57,270
"An Orphan from Syria."

325
00:23:57,353 --> 00:24:00,773
Su-ho grew up in an orphanage.

326
00:24:01,482 --> 00:24:03,442
His situation was a lot like mine.

327
00:24:07,947 --> 00:24:08,948
[Woo-seok sighs]

328
00:24:09,031 --> 00:24:13,536
[Seol-ah] Just how much did
Mr. Paek learn about me?

329
00:24:15,872 --> 00:24:19,167
He seems to know
just as much about me as Su-ho.

330
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:26,465
Let's go over everything one by one
and figure out who he is.

331
00:24:27,842 --> 00:24:30,720
[dramatic music plays]

332
00:24:34,056 --> 00:24:37,435
Could you tell me the exact reason
you were fired from Your Home?

333
00:24:37,518 --> 00:24:41,355
Until he left for Syria,
I managed his schedule every day

334
00:24:41,439 --> 00:24:44,025
and took care
of just about everything for him.

335
00:24:44,108 --> 00:24:46,652
But when he came back,
he suddenly told me to leave.

336
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:50,406
Everyone who had been there
from the beginning was let go as well.

337
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:54,285
[clicks tongue] Is there anything else
you remember from that time?

338
00:24:55,077 --> 00:24:56,078
Hmm…

339
00:24:56,704 --> 00:25:02,210
The security system in places like the
office and the lab kept malfunctioning.

340
00:25:02,293 --> 00:25:06,255
It had been set up exclusively for
the CEO, but the errors kept happening,

341
00:25:06,339 --> 00:25:08,966
and in the end he told them
to replace the entire system.

342
00:25:09,592 --> 00:25:10,801
Errors?

343
00:25:10,885 --> 00:25:13,679
The system was designed
to scan the iris and grant access,

344
00:25:14,180 --> 00:25:17,391
but for some reason it kept failing
to recognize Mr. Paek.

345
00:25:18,851 --> 00:25:22,605
So they brought in the security company
and they had to replace the whole system.

346
00:25:23,773 --> 00:25:27,193
He wasn't recognized
even though it was him?

347
00:25:27,276 --> 00:25:28,527
Right.

348
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:34,158
His iris is different?

349
00:25:34,242 --> 00:25:37,787
Even with surgery, there's
no way to change your iris pattern.

350
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:41,332
He might be someone else
wearing Paek Jun-beom's face.

351
00:25:41,832 --> 00:25:43,793
[Eun-hyuk] Here. What you asked for.

352
00:25:44,293 --> 00:25:45,586
Oh, thanks.

353
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:49,131
Why did you ask me
to gather photos of this guy?

354
00:25:49,215 --> 00:25:50,883
[chuckles] I promise I'll tell you later.

355
00:25:50,967 --> 00:25:52,593
Where are you going?

356
00:25:53,886 --> 00:25:57,014
Are you going around
investigating Paek Jun-beom?

357
00:26:02,853 --> 00:26:05,940
Paek Jun-beom.
He was friends with Lee Su-ho?

358
00:26:06,023 --> 00:26:08,609
Yes, and he approached me on purpose.

359
00:26:09,443 --> 00:26:12,321
I need to find out exactly
what his real intentions are.

360
00:26:12,405 --> 00:26:14,490
Are you saying that everything
that's happened to you

361
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,783
wasn't just a coincidence?

362
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:19,745
Mmm. That's exactly what I think.

363
00:26:20,454 --> 00:26:21,706
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

364
00:26:21,789 --> 00:26:26,294
You should've come to me first
and not that insurance investigator.

365
00:26:26,377 --> 00:26:30,548
He and I are just sharing information
because we need it.

366
00:26:31,173 --> 00:26:33,217
Well, I'm kind of hurt.

367
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:37,013
Feels like you're relying
on him more than me.

368
00:26:38,514 --> 00:26:39,765
It's not like that.

369
00:26:41,350 --> 00:26:43,519
He's kind of like us, you know.

370
00:26:45,062 --> 00:26:49,358
We just recognized that
in each other, like you and me.

371
00:26:56,115 --> 00:26:57,950
[friend] Yeah, I know Paek Jun-beom well.

372
00:26:58,826 --> 00:27:02,038
I heard you two were in a start-up club
together back in college.

373
00:27:02,913 --> 00:27:05,583
He used to really take care
of everyone around him,

374
00:27:06,083 --> 00:27:08,794
but a lot of people say
he's become a different person now.

375
00:27:09,462 --> 00:27:12,048
So you're not in contact
with him at all now?

376
00:27:12,131 --> 00:27:13,883
There were rumors that he'd hurt his face,

377
00:27:13,966 --> 00:27:16,802
so I thought maybe that's why
he was avoiding people,

378
00:27:16,886 --> 00:27:18,971
but I saw him at a conference
and he looked fine.

379
00:27:19,055 --> 00:27:21,682
He even seemed
a bit more handsome. [chuckles]

380
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:24,560
But when I said hi,
he just treated me like I was a stranger.

381
00:27:25,478 --> 00:27:28,189
I hear his other friends
also lost contact with him.

382
00:27:28,272 --> 00:27:29,357
Do you happen to know why?

383
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,984
[inhales sharply]
I'm curious about that too.

384
00:27:32,068 --> 00:27:34,070
How can someone change that much?

385
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:39,825
That bastard put the poison in, like this.

386
00:27:39,909 --> 00:27:41,494
[exclaiming]

387
00:27:41,577 --> 00:27:42,787
I watched, squinting.

388
00:27:42,870 --> 00:27:44,914
And then I broke out in a cold sweat.

389
00:27:44,997 --> 00:27:47,333
Cold sweat just kept dripping
down my back.

390
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:50,086
- And then?
- I just pretended to be asleep.

391
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:52,671
Yikes. If you'd actually had the IV in,

392
00:27:52,755 --> 00:27:55,007
you could've ended up dead instead of me.

393
00:27:55,091 --> 00:27:57,343
Yeah. I risked my life to pull this off.

394
00:27:57,426 --> 00:28:00,388
I was ready to take that bastard on
in hand-to-hand combat

395
00:28:00,471 --> 00:28:01,680
if he saw I was a fake.

396
00:28:01,764 --> 00:28:04,892
Wow. You used
to be a detective too, right?

397
00:28:05,476 --> 00:28:06,727
[smacks lips] Oh, no.

398
00:28:07,395 --> 00:28:09,688
I'm more of the smart type.
I got in through the exam.

399
00:28:10,815 --> 00:28:13,692
Well, anyway,
thank goodness we didn't get caught.

400
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:17,738
We even kind of look alike
with our faces covered, don't you think?

401
00:28:18,739 --> 00:28:19,740
No, we don't.

402
00:28:22,868 --> 00:28:25,037
[gasps] Can you call Mr. Cha, please?

403
00:28:26,414 --> 00:28:27,415
[Kwang-jin] <i>DNA.</i>

404
00:28:29,542 --> 00:28:32,253
Since we often go into conflict zones,

405
00:28:32,336 --> 00:28:35,506
we keep DNA samples
for identification just in case.

406
00:28:35,589 --> 00:28:38,509
OnWorld has Su-ho
and Jun-beom's DNA on file.

407
00:28:41,011 --> 00:28:45,015
We can finally find out
what Paek Jun-beom wanted to hide.

408
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:21,677
{\an8}KIM JOON-YOUNG

409
00:30:10,184 --> 00:30:11,185
An invitation?

410
00:30:11,268 --> 00:30:15,314
Yes, it's for a preview event
for our VIP guests.

411
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:19,235
And it's also the first public showing
of the Stiller piece.

412
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:20,569
Yes, I should be there.

413
00:30:20,653 --> 00:30:22,446
That's my beloved child after all.

414
00:30:56,647 --> 00:31:00,943
In 2013, Stiller sought
to visualize the "layers of memory."

415
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:06,657
The densely applied blue paint, along
with the repeating geometric patterns,

416
00:31:06,740 --> 00:31:11,287
functioned as a metaphor
for the accumulation and erosion of time.

417
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:14,164
The red lines, reminiscent of frames,

418
00:31:14,248 --> 00:31:18,002
were employed
to heighten a sense of disorientation.

419
00:31:18,085 --> 00:31:21,714
Through this approach,
Stiller captured what he described as

420
00:31:21,797 --> 00:31:24,008
"the moment when memory
consumes its own borders."

421
00:31:27,678 --> 00:31:28,971
[whispers] Look, it's him.

422
00:31:29,555 --> 00:31:31,640
[person 1] He's way better-looking
than the rumors said.

423
00:31:31,724 --> 00:31:33,601
And he's still single.

424
00:31:44,612 --> 00:31:46,572
Mr. Lee Kwang-jin says hello.

425
00:31:48,532 --> 00:31:50,034
He's doing well,

426
00:31:51,702 --> 00:31:52,870
and he misses you.

427
00:31:56,832 --> 00:31:57,833
I'm glad to hear.

428
00:31:58,834 --> 00:32:01,879
Mr. Lee is actually the only person
I really miss too.

429
00:32:03,047 --> 00:32:05,132
Hmm, I see.

430
00:32:06,592 --> 00:32:09,053
[scoffs, inhales sharply]

431
00:32:09,887 --> 00:32:11,847
Do you usually act differently
from how you feel?

432
00:32:13,974 --> 00:32:16,185
Why not make the wise choice this time?

433
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:20,689
Going to the police
voluntarily looks better.

434
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,192
It could get you a lighter sentence

435
00:32:24,151 --> 00:32:25,194
instead of getting caught.

436
00:32:28,072 --> 00:32:32,451
It sounds like it would be lost of fun,
but I doubt that I'll ever get the chance.

437
00:32:33,911 --> 00:32:36,330
Our legal team works
way too hard these days.

438
00:32:38,457 --> 00:32:39,583
[scoffs]

439
00:32:39,667 --> 00:32:42,044
You must be very upset
about the whole accident, sir.

440
00:32:42,127 --> 00:32:43,128
185TH MAJOR AUCTION

441
00:32:43,212 --> 00:32:46,548
The paintings have appreciated several
times over, so the losses are huge.

442
00:32:46,632 --> 00:32:47,633
And it's not just one.

443
00:32:47,716 --> 00:32:51,303
You've got insurance
for exactly this kind of situation.

444
00:32:52,137 --> 00:32:56,684
Ms. Han, I hear you know
the insurance account manager.

445
00:32:56,767 --> 00:33:00,229
- [visitor] You do?
- Make sure that they take good care of it.

446
00:33:01,063 --> 00:33:02,356
Yes. Of course, ma'am.

447
00:33:03,148 --> 00:33:04,650
Put your worries to rest.

448
00:33:04,733 --> 00:33:06,652
You know Ms. Han's great at what she does.

449
00:33:06,735 --> 00:33:07,986
[chuckles]

450
00:33:08,070 --> 00:33:12,241
Once you get the compensation,
you can buy even better paintings.

451
00:33:12,324 --> 00:33:16,036
I'll pick out some good ones
for you again. [chuckles]

452
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:20,374
This here is a Stiller piece
coming up in the next auction.

453
00:33:21,542 --> 00:33:23,168
Stiller works are rare,

454
00:33:23,252 --> 00:33:26,839
and since this is the first time
going to auction in the country,

455
00:33:26,922 --> 00:33:29,216
the competition will be fierce…

456
00:33:29,299 --> 00:33:31,260
But I'm sure that you can…

457
00:33:36,515 --> 00:33:40,060
Mr. Paek, Chair Kim would like
to meet with you privately.

458
00:33:40,144 --> 00:33:41,270
Is that okay?

459
00:33:42,312 --> 00:33:43,480
Sure, that's fine.

460
00:33:46,108 --> 00:33:49,194
I guess I'm just not really
cut out for parties.

461
00:33:52,197 --> 00:33:53,574
I feel uncomfortable.

462
00:33:54,992 --> 00:33:55,993
[Seol-ah chuckles]

463
00:33:56,744 --> 00:34:00,372
Times like these
call for a moment to relax.

464
00:34:01,165 --> 00:34:02,166
[Jun-beom] Hmm.

465
00:34:16,430 --> 00:34:18,474
[chuckles] You're working now.

466
00:34:19,308 --> 00:34:20,309
Yes.

467
00:34:23,645 --> 00:34:26,356
[coughing]

468
00:34:33,614 --> 00:34:34,865
Is something wrong?

469
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,160
[Jun-beom chokes, groans]

470
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:40,329
- Mr. Paek!
- [crowd murmuring]

471
00:34:40,996 --> 00:34:42,956
Mr. Paek Jun-beom, can you hear me?

472
00:34:43,040 --> 00:34:44,708
[choking, straining]

473
00:34:53,425 --> 00:34:55,052
What's wrong with him?

474
00:34:57,262 --> 00:34:59,181
It looks like anaphylactic shock.

475
00:34:59,264 --> 00:35:01,016
With this condition,
he should have an EpiPen.

476
00:35:07,689 --> 00:35:10,692
[straining continues]

477
00:35:17,324 --> 00:35:19,618
[panting]

478
00:35:19,701 --> 00:35:21,537
[murmuring continues]

479
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:23,163
[breathes heavily]

480
00:35:23,247 --> 00:35:25,249
[visitor 2] How come nobody's called
the ambulance yet?

481
00:35:26,542 --> 00:35:28,293
- Oh, my God.
- [intense music plays]

482
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:30,879
[visitor 3] What's going on?

483
00:35:30,963 --> 00:35:33,423
[crowd continues murmuring]

484
00:35:43,267 --> 00:35:45,727
- [visitor 2] Is he breathing?
- [visitor 3] What's going on here?

485
00:35:45,811 --> 00:35:47,020
What's wrong with him?

486
00:35:58,574 --> 00:36:00,951
[line rings, clicks]

487
00:36:01,034 --> 00:36:02,578
Where are you? Hurry.

488
00:36:07,833 --> 00:36:08,834
[grunts]

489
00:36:09,543 --> 00:36:11,044
Got the sample?

490
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:13,755
- Yeah.
- Huh?

491
00:36:14,673 --> 00:36:15,799
[wheezing]

492
00:36:20,095 --> 00:36:21,930
What exactly did you do?

493
00:36:22,014 --> 00:36:24,141
We'll get totally accurate results.

494
00:36:24,224 --> 00:36:25,642
- Step on it.
- Yes, sir.

495
00:36:31,106 --> 00:36:33,108
[breathing shakily]

496
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,204
It looks like anaphylactic shock.

497
00:36:46,288 --> 00:36:48,415
With this condition,
he should have an EpiPen.

498
00:36:51,501 --> 00:36:53,629
[breathes shakily]

499
00:36:53,712 --> 00:36:56,214
[Jun-beom] <i>I watched Su-ho</i>
<i>be happy and sad,</i>

500
00:36:56,298 --> 00:36:59,968
<i>also tormented all because of</i>
<i>a woman named Han Seol-ah.</i>

501
00:37:00,052 --> 00:37:01,553
<i>And I always wondered,</i>

502
00:37:02,888 --> 00:37:05,140
- "What kind of person is she?"
- [breathes shakily]

503
00:37:05,223 --> 00:37:10,312
If Su-ho were still alive, I wouldn't have
dared to even think about it.

504
00:37:10,896 --> 00:37:12,898
But my friend's no longer in this world,

505
00:37:14,149 --> 00:37:17,903
and you and I are here,
under the same sky.

506
00:37:21,031 --> 00:37:23,033
[breathing shakily]

507
00:37:34,252 --> 00:37:37,005
[sighs] What's all this commotion
at a VIP event?

508
00:37:37,089 --> 00:37:38,465
Geez. [clicks tongue]

509
00:37:38,548 --> 00:37:40,175
Mr. Song! Wait.

510
00:37:41,218 --> 00:37:42,219
Hey, come here.

511
00:37:43,720 --> 00:37:46,264
You were serving earlier.
What the hell happened?

512
00:37:46,348 --> 00:37:49,851
[sighs] Mr. Paek suddenly collapsed
while drinking champagne.

513
00:37:50,978 --> 00:37:52,187
But more importantly…

514
00:37:53,188 --> 00:37:54,189
What's this?

515
00:37:56,233 --> 00:38:01,405
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

516
00:38:04,199 --> 00:38:07,077
{\an8}1 / JULIAN VANCE
2 / ELENA MONTGOMERY

517
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:09,621
What's all this?

518
00:38:09,705 --> 00:38:11,456
It's from Han Seol-ah's desk.

519
00:38:11,540 --> 00:38:13,834
I grabbed it
while all that commotion was going on.

520
00:38:14,751 --> 00:38:16,628
You've got some nerve, huh?

521
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:18,922
You told me not to slack off.

522
00:38:19,006 --> 00:38:20,215
Right.

523
00:38:24,177 --> 00:38:25,512
Oh, man.

524
00:38:26,388 --> 00:38:29,433
You see, people always
bite the hand that feeds them.

525
00:38:30,392 --> 00:38:33,603
So she's been snooping around
behind Chair Kim's back?

526
00:39:07,929 --> 00:39:09,890
110 over 70.

527
00:39:14,269 --> 00:39:18,231
It's back to normal now.
But should we keep Dr. Jeong on standby?

528
00:39:19,357 --> 00:39:20,484
It's fine.

529
00:39:38,752 --> 00:39:39,878
Have a seat.

530
00:39:48,678 --> 00:39:50,180
Is the event over?

531
00:39:52,516 --> 00:39:53,558
Not yet.

532
00:39:55,435 --> 00:39:56,937
Why are you here?

533
00:39:58,105 --> 00:40:00,732
I don't think
I'll get another chance like today.

534
00:40:05,987 --> 00:40:10,617
So isn't there something
that you want to tell me?

535
00:40:15,205 --> 00:40:16,832
We finally ended up here.

536
00:40:21,253 --> 00:40:22,879
There's somewhere I wanna take you.

537
00:40:24,881 --> 00:40:26,633
I have something to show you.

538
00:41:10,218 --> 00:41:11,386
[car door opens]

539
00:41:25,901 --> 00:41:27,903
[dramatic music plays]

540
00:42:02,854 --> 00:42:04,314
[Su-ho] <i>Someday, later on,</i>

541
00:42:05,065 --> 00:42:08,235
I want us to build a house
somewhere in the woods.

542
00:42:09,069 --> 00:42:11,196
- [Seol-ah] Hmm?
- A two-story house.

543
00:42:12,489 --> 00:42:13,740
[chuckles]

544
00:42:16,576 --> 00:42:18,620
[Su-ho] <i>I want it to have a big yard,</i>

545
00:42:19,329 --> 00:42:21,373
<i>big enough</i>
<i>for the kids to run around all day.</i>

546
00:42:22,374 --> 00:42:24,084
<i>Along the path to the house,</i>

547
00:42:25,460 --> 00:42:27,587
<i>I'll plant birch trees, which you love.</i>

548
00:42:28,380 --> 00:42:33,927
<i>On the lawn, I'll set up a small swing,</i>
<i>so you can ride it with the kids anytime.</i>

549
00:42:38,556 --> 00:42:39,599
[phone buzzes]

550
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:43,436
SEOL-AH, WHERE ARE YOU?

551
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:45,230
[Woo-seok] <i>Where are you, Seol-ah?</i>

552
00:42:48,483 --> 00:42:49,484
POWERING OFF…

553
00:43:02,706 --> 00:43:04,958
The first year, I cleared the land.

554
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,835
The next year, I built the house.

555
00:43:08,628 --> 00:43:10,672
From the stonework to the roof,

556
00:43:11,798 --> 00:43:13,591
even every single tree,

557
00:43:15,093 --> 00:43:16,845
my hand is in all of it.

558
00:43:21,683 --> 00:43:23,977
I wanted you
to be the first to see it, Seol-ah.

559
00:43:26,855 --> 00:43:28,440
Aren't you cold?

560
00:43:28,523 --> 00:43:29,607
Just hold on.

561
00:43:32,235 --> 00:43:33,903
Oh, right.

562
00:43:33,987 --> 00:43:35,322
No fire.

563
00:43:39,492 --> 00:43:40,577
Su-ho.

564
00:43:56,134 --> 00:43:58,887
The blood in the syringe you brought
was compared against two samples,

565
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:00,638
Lee Su-ho and Paek Jun-beom.

566
00:44:00,722 --> 00:44:06,144
We got the results, and the STR profile
is consistent with Lee Su-ho.

567
00:44:11,816 --> 00:44:13,943
TEST RESULTS - SHARED ALLELES
OF SAMPLE 1 AND 2 - MATCH

568
00:44:15,987 --> 00:44:17,822
SAMPLE 1 - LEE SU-HO
SAMPLE 2 - PAEK JUN-BEOM

569
00:44:20,033 --> 00:44:21,701
MATCHES BETWEEN
SAMPLE 1 AND SAMPLE 2.

570
00:44:21,785 --> 00:44:23,995
THEREFORE, SAMPLE 1 AND SAMPLE
2 ARE FROM THE SAME INDIVIDUAL.

571
00:44:24,079 --> 00:44:25,622
So, he's not Paek Jun-beom.

572
00:44:25,705 --> 00:44:27,248
That means he's Lee Su-ho.

573
00:44:27,874 --> 00:44:29,667
Paek Jun-beom died in Syria.

574
00:44:31,711 --> 00:44:33,713
[breathing heavily]

575
00:44:36,216 --> 00:44:38,301
[automated voice] <i>The phone you are trying</i>
<i>to reach is turned off.</i>

576
00:44:38,385 --> 00:44:39,844
<i>You will be directed to voicemail after…</i>

577
00:44:42,138 --> 00:44:43,139
[colleague] Mr. Cha!

578
00:44:59,781 --> 00:45:01,783
[interesting music plays]

579
00:45:43,658 --> 00:45:46,286
It had started
to feel like someone else's name…

580
00:45:47,912 --> 00:45:48,913
[sighs]

581
00:45:49,622 --> 00:45:51,458
…but hearing you say it

582
00:45:52,792 --> 00:45:55,086
feels like I'm back in the old days.

583
00:45:58,965 --> 00:46:00,758
Honestly, I was worried.

584
00:46:03,344 --> 00:46:05,346
"What if she recognizes me?" I thought.

585
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:07,807
But I was

586
00:46:09,225 --> 00:46:10,935
Paek Jun-beom, the VIP.

587
00:46:12,687 --> 00:46:14,606
You only looked at the painting I had.

588
00:46:16,774 --> 00:46:17,775
Come on.

589
00:46:18,943 --> 00:46:21,070
You were testing if it was me,
weren't you?

590
00:46:23,072 --> 00:46:25,617
Didn't you put something in the champagne?

591
00:46:27,702 --> 00:46:29,204
But how could you be…

592
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:31,164
Lee Su-ho?

593
00:46:31,998 --> 00:46:32,999
[gate beeps]

594
00:46:33,875 --> 00:46:34,876
Seol-ah.

595
00:46:38,087 --> 00:46:40,340
[Chair Kim] <i>He's at the TH Hotel.</i>
<i>Take good care of him.</i>

596
00:46:40,423 --> 00:46:43,051
[sighs] What's with you?
I'm late for my meeting.

597
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:46,095
Come on. I'm leaving for Syria tomorrow.

598
00:46:46,179 --> 00:46:47,889
I already told you.

599
00:46:48,515 --> 00:46:50,308
Work is more important to me.

600
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:52,894
So everything's different
now that you work here?

601
00:46:52,977 --> 00:46:55,813
You think there's no future
with someone like me?

602
00:46:56,898 --> 00:46:57,899
[Seol-ah grunts]

603
00:47:02,278 --> 00:47:03,279
[sighs]

604
00:47:04,781 --> 00:47:06,991
SEOL-AH

605
00:47:07,075 --> 00:47:08,076
CALLING…
SEOL-AH

606
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:09,202
- [phone beeps]
- [line rings]

607
00:47:09,285 --> 00:47:11,037
[phone buzzes]

608
00:47:30,682 --> 00:47:31,683
[sighs]

609
00:47:40,316 --> 00:47:42,443
I'm… [chuckles]

610
00:47:44,279 --> 00:47:47,532
You killed me. [laughs]

611
00:47:47,615 --> 00:47:48,741
[Jun-beom] <i>Not anymore.</i>

612
00:47:49,534 --> 00:47:53,913
The idiot who chose death just so
Han Seol-ah would remember him forever…

613
00:47:57,417 --> 00:47:58,668
is dead.

614
00:48:03,047 --> 00:48:04,882
Funny how life works.

615
00:48:05,508 --> 00:48:09,804
Of all days, Jun-beom and I happened
to be wearing each other's clothes.

616
00:48:09,887 --> 00:48:12,223
- [people exclaiming]
- [Kwang-jin] Jun-beom, stay with me.

617
00:48:12,307 --> 00:48:13,683
You're going to be okay, Jun-beom.

618
00:48:13,766 --> 00:48:16,561
Just hang in there.
Jun-beom, you'll be okay. Stay with me.

619
00:48:16,644 --> 00:48:18,563
- Excuse me, move!
- This way.

620
00:48:20,148 --> 00:48:22,525
[Jun-beom] <i>The friend</i>
<i>who came to save me died.</i>

621
00:48:23,026 --> 00:48:24,944
<i>And I was the one who survived.</i>

622
00:48:25,028 --> 00:48:26,571
{\an8}06 - PAEK JUN-**** - IN SURGERY

623
00:48:26,654 --> 00:48:27,655
CENTRAL OPERATING ROOM

624
00:48:27,739 --> 00:48:30,199
<i>The medical staff thought I was</i>
<i>Paek Jun-beom.</i>

625
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:39,208
<i>I had to undergo reconstructive surgery</i>
<i>on my blown-out face and vocal cords.</i>

626
00:48:48,843 --> 00:48:50,970
<i>After dozens of surgeries,</i>

627
00:48:52,472 --> 00:48:54,474
<i>I took on my friend's face.</i>

628
00:48:57,518 --> 00:48:59,520
Along with my face and name…

629
00:49:02,357 --> 00:49:03,816
even my voice changed.

630
00:49:05,276 --> 00:49:07,195
And I had to live in the world again…

631
00:49:09,906 --> 00:49:11,240
as Paek Jun-beom.

632
00:49:13,326 --> 00:49:17,455
When I came back,
I realized how stupid it all was.

633
00:49:18,665 --> 00:49:21,334
You didn't care at all
whether I lived or died.

634
00:49:21,417 --> 00:49:23,378
[laughs]

635
00:49:23,461 --> 00:49:25,505
Did you really like money that much?

636
00:49:25,588 --> 00:49:28,132
Enough to go to a hotel with some old man?

637
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:30,468
That was work.

638
00:49:30,551 --> 00:49:33,346
It wasn't anything like
what you're thinking… [sighs]

639
00:49:34,472 --> 00:49:36,307
So what are you doing here now?

640
00:49:36,391 --> 00:49:39,811
The Lee Su-ho you dumped
was utterly pathetic,

641
00:49:40,353 --> 00:49:42,730
but Paek Jun-beom's life was different.

642
00:49:56,077 --> 00:49:58,121
This is the private viewing room
of our auction house.

643
00:49:58,204 --> 00:50:00,123
I'll escort you inside, sir.

644
00:50:06,212 --> 00:50:08,923
[Seol-ah] Bidder number 86, 3.7 million.

645
00:50:09,674 --> 00:50:11,426
Congratulations.

646
00:50:16,806 --> 00:50:19,559
[Jun-beom] <i>So this is how</i>
<i>sweet and comfortable success is.</i>

647
00:50:20,351 --> 00:50:21,811
It makes you confident.

648
00:50:23,146 --> 00:50:24,814
I just didn't know that world.

649
00:50:24,897 --> 00:50:26,149
And then

650
00:50:26,858 --> 00:50:28,359
I started wondering…

651
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:35,783
"With this much money,
wouldn't I be able to tempt her?"

652
00:50:37,994 --> 00:50:41,664
But part of me was hoping
you wouldn't fall for it.

653
00:50:44,375 --> 00:50:45,376
[breathes shakily]

654
00:50:46,961 --> 00:50:47,962
[breathing shakily]

655
00:50:48,755 --> 00:50:52,717
You really are Lee Su-ho.

656
00:50:54,010 --> 00:50:55,762
Lee Su-ho the fool.

657
00:50:57,638 --> 00:51:00,975
When you have nothing, the only thing
you can throw away is yourself.

658
00:51:01,642 --> 00:51:04,061
I hated you as much as I loved you.

659
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:08,608
I wanted revenge, even if
it meant dying. [breathing heavily]

660
00:51:10,109 --> 00:51:12,069
[Woo-seok]
I'm at Paek Jun-beom's house. [grunts]

661
00:51:12,153 --> 00:51:13,613
Shit. [breathes heavily]

662
00:51:14,655 --> 00:51:16,824
I can't reach either of them.
Track their location.

663
00:51:16,908 --> 00:51:18,493
You need to move now!

664
00:51:19,660 --> 00:51:21,245
Don't you know Captain Pyo?

665
00:51:21,329 --> 00:51:23,748
You know he won't roll out
for something like that.

666
00:51:23,831 --> 00:51:25,249
What's going on?

667
00:51:25,333 --> 00:51:28,127
I don't have time to explain.
[breathing heavily]

668
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:31,088
Then tell him to come
and arrest me in the act.

669
00:51:31,172 --> 00:51:32,548
What are you going to do?

670
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:35,176
I'm going to kill Paek Jun-beom.

671
00:51:36,135 --> 00:51:37,762
- [Gong] <i>Hey, Cha Woo-seok!</i>
- [phone beeps]

672
00:51:37,845 --> 00:51:39,722
[sighs] Shit.

673
00:51:45,228 --> 00:51:47,230
[alarm blaring]

674
00:51:49,357 --> 00:51:51,359
[breathing heavily]

675
00:52:07,834 --> 00:52:09,126
[grunts]

676
00:52:11,254 --> 00:52:13,673
[grunting]

677
00:52:30,940 --> 00:52:32,358
APPROACHED SEOL-AH
AFTER KIM YUN-JI CASE

678
00:52:32,441 --> 00:52:33,442
FAINTED AT TAEMYUNG
ART CENTER

679
00:52:34,735 --> 00:52:35,736
SUK-JI
OBSESSED WITH SEOL-AH

680
00:52:35,820 --> 00:52:36,904
EUN-HYUK
MORE THAN A FRIEND?

681
00:52:36,988 --> 00:52:38,781
YUN-JI - OWNED UNIT,
"ACROSS FROM SEOL-AH'S PLACE,"

682
00:52:38,865 --> 00:52:40,324
CHA WOO-SEOK RESIGNED

683
00:52:41,492 --> 00:52:42,618
2024 TO 2025
ROMANCE & PROPOSAL

684
00:52:42,702 --> 00:52:43,703
DATED, THEN PROPOSED

685
00:52:43,786 --> 00:52:45,037
YOON SEUNG-JAE
RAN GALLERY RESTAURANT

686
00:52:52,253 --> 00:52:53,504
[breathes shakily]

687
00:52:53,588 --> 00:52:55,923
{\an8}HAN SEOL-AH

688
00:52:56,007 --> 00:52:57,049
{\an8}[breathes shakily]

689
00:52:57,550 --> 00:52:58,634
SEOL-AH AFTER WORK
NOT AS ME…

690
00:52:58,718 --> 00:53:00,011
SEOL-AH
SEOL-AH RUNNING AN AUCTION

691
00:53:00,094 --> 00:53:01,762
[breathing heavily]

692
00:53:04,682 --> 00:53:07,059
And if I'd come back as Lee Su-ho,

693
00:53:07,977 --> 00:53:10,146
would you have even noticed me?
[inhales sharply]

694
00:53:10,229 --> 00:53:13,482
Only after I won that million-dollar bid
did you finally look at me.

695
00:53:13,566 --> 00:53:15,610
And when you found out
I had that Stiller piece,

696
00:53:15,693 --> 00:53:17,403
you came, wagging your tail!

697
00:53:17,486 --> 00:53:18,863
[breathes heavily]

698
00:53:18,946 --> 00:53:24,201
And like a moron,
I wavered again when I saw you like that.

699
00:53:26,662 --> 00:53:29,373
[inhales sharply] I wanted
to make you my woman again!

700
00:53:29,457 --> 00:53:31,334
[breathing heavily]

701
00:53:31,417 --> 00:53:33,169
We can be happy, Seol-ah.

702
00:53:33,252 --> 00:53:35,046
I'm Paek Jun-beom now, I can do anything.

703
00:53:35,129 --> 00:53:36,631
I'll give you whatever you want, okay?

704
00:53:36,714 --> 00:53:38,257
- You've completely lost it!
- Okay?

705
00:53:38,341 --> 00:53:40,343
[laughing]

706
00:53:41,636 --> 00:53:44,597
- Why not? Huh? [chuckles]
- [Seol-ah breathes shakily]

707
00:53:45,473 --> 00:53:46,474
What?

708
00:53:49,185 --> 00:53:51,896
Really? Because of Cha Woo-seok?

709
00:53:55,024 --> 00:53:56,859
[breathes shakily]

710
00:53:57,777 --> 00:53:59,278
You like that bastard?

711
00:54:00,112 --> 00:54:02,114
[siren wailing]

712
00:54:05,952 --> 00:54:07,161
[sighs]

713
00:54:10,247 --> 00:54:11,374
[sighs]

714
00:54:12,166 --> 00:54:13,709
DO EUN-HYUK
MORE THAN JUST A FRIEND?

715
00:54:13,793 --> 00:54:15,836
DO EUN-HYE SEEMS TO
DISLIKE HAN SEOL-AH - HOSTILE

716
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:18,881
[sighs]

717
00:54:21,133 --> 00:54:22,510
Hurry up and decide.

718
00:54:35,147 --> 00:54:37,191
- [radio beeps]
- Get Paek Jun-beom's location now

719
00:54:37,274 --> 00:54:38,609
and deploy all units.

720
00:54:38,693 --> 00:54:39,694
[radio beeps]

721
00:54:40,820 --> 00:54:41,988
Uncuff him.

722
00:54:48,077 --> 00:54:50,079
[siren wailing]

723
00:54:59,338 --> 00:55:03,426
Last ping before the signal dropped was
866, Jicheon-myeon, Yangpyeong-gun.

724
00:55:06,554 --> 00:55:08,931
[gasps] No!

725
00:55:09,015 --> 00:55:11,684
[whimpering] Get off me! Let go of me!

726
00:55:14,603 --> 00:55:15,771
[breathing shakily]

727
00:55:15,855 --> 00:55:16,856
Stay away.

728
00:55:17,857 --> 00:55:19,817
[laughs]

729
00:55:19,900 --> 00:55:21,277
Don't do this.

730
00:55:22,361 --> 00:55:24,280
I already died once because of you.

731
00:55:25,239 --> 00:55:27,241
Why not make it twice now?

732
00:55:28,784 --> 00:55:33,539
In this life,
I'm not letting you go, Seol-ah.

733
00:55:33,622 --> 00:55:35,249
[sobbing]

734
00:55:38,502 --> 00:55:40,504
[both breathing heavily]

735
00:55:41,213 --> 00:55:43,299
Huh? [breathes heavily]

736
00:56:01,942 --> 00:56:02,943
CALLING…
HAN SEOL-AH

737
00:56:03,027 --> 00:56:05,154
[automated voice] <i>The phone you are</i>
<i>trying to reach is turned off.</i>

738
00:56:05,237 --> 00:56:07,531
<i>You will be directed to voicemail</i>
<i>after the beep and charges will apply.</i>

739
00:56:07,615 --> 00:56:08,616
CALL ENDED
HAN SEOL-AH

740
00:58:06,692 --> 00:58:07,860
Don't move.

741
00:58:53,530 --> 00:58:54,782
[gasps]

742
00:58:57,076 --> 00:58:58,077
[breathes shakily]

743
00:59:01,580 --> 00:59:02,581
[breathes shakily]

744
00:59:44,707 --> 00:59:47,042
{\an8}- Let go!
- This is a murder case!

745
00:59:47,626 --> 00:59:49,211
{\an8}Let me see her just once.

746
00:59:49,295 --> 00:59:51,422
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>Everyone said</i>
<i>they just pitied me</i>

747
00:59:52,381 --> 00:59:54,216
{\an8}<i>that they'd do anything for me,</i>

748
00:59:54,300 --> 00:59:58,971
{\an8}so I told them to do what my parents did,
to get insurance and die.

749
00:59:59,680 --> 01:00:01,307
{\an8}[Woo-seok] <i>If someone else was involved…</i>

750
01:00:02,057 --> 01:00:05,602
{\an8}Don't let your guard down. She's still
the prime suspect of the investigation.

751
01:00:05,686 --> 01:00:08,147
{\an8}Cha Woo-seok really cares.

752
01:00:08,230 --> 01:00:09,648
{\an8}[Seol-ah] <i>Thank you so much</i>

753
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:14,570
{\an8}<i>for helping me and trusting me.</i>

